Difference Between Revert and Original Commits

Original Commits

Original commits add or modify content.

Example:

First Commit  → Added PRN
Second Commit → Added Full Name
Third Commit  → Added Welcome Message and Date

These commits move repository forward.

---

Revert Commits

Revert commits create NEW commits that undo previous changes.

Example:

Revert Third Commit
Revert Second Commit

Advantages:

- Preserves commit history
- Safe for shared repositories
- No commit deletion

---

Why Use Revert Instead of Reset?

git revert

git revert <commit-id>

- Keeps history intact
- Creates new commit
- Safe for collaborative projects

git reset

git reset --hard <commit-id>

- Removes commits from history
- Dangerous after push
- Rewrites repository history

